14 Jun 2015 West Africa: Ebola could hit again - MSF
http://www.iol.co.za/news/africa/ebola-could-hit-again-msf-1.1871408#.VX2rslLLLnk
[According to Joanne Liu, international president of Medecins Sans Frontieres (MSF), the Ebola epidemic could reignite in West Africa and health authorities are no better equipped to control it than they were a year ago. It is doubtful the effect of the response would be improved from that in the flare-up in August and September 2014, Ms. Liu said.MSF has been disappointed by the recommendations of the World Health Assembly, and, again, by the G7 (Group of 7). She was also referencing the May 2015 meeting of the World Health Organization (WHO)... MSF's head of Guinea's Ebola response efforts, Jerome Mouton, indicated there is a state of "semi-denial" about the reality of the Ebola virus outbreak, similar to a year ago, with another major flare-up being possible. According to Mouton, while some say the outbreak is "almost finished," in reality it is not.]

12 Jun 2015 Liberia: 'Don't travel to Sierra Leone, Guinea'
http://allafrica.com/stories/201506121706.html
[The Government of Liberia has issued a travel and health alert, warning Liberians to avoid traveling to Guinea and Sierra Leone [because of active transmission in those 2 countries... Liberia needs to help her 2 neighbors to get to zero because the 2 countries have several porous borders with Liberia]
[It would be most helpful for the 3 countries to work together to eliminate Ebola transmission, since the borders do not serve as a barrier to movement of the virus. - Mod.LK]

11 Jun 2015 West Africa: Ebola health personnel who return from West Africa face stigma of virus
