Research, drugs, vaccines
--------

12 Jun 2015 China: Ebola drug raises hopes, and rancor
http://www.nytimes.com/2015/06/12/world/chinese-ebola-drug-brings-american-objections.html?partner=rss&emc=rss&_r=0
[The Chinese drug, MIL77, was used for the recent Ebola infection case in Italy and for a British Army nurse in March 2015, with "miraculous" effects. The issue: MIL77 is a "near copy" of Zmapp which is a product of a collaboration between the United States and Canada]
[While a limited supply of American ZMapp was quickly exhausted, a small private Chinese company, Beijing Mabworks, raced ahead in the fall of 2014, helping to produce about 100 doses of MIL77 in animal cells rather than tobacco plants. This is good news for desperate patients, but it also has led to patent infringement concerns by American officials. Also at issue is disagreements over when unapproved Ebola therapies should be offered to patients only in carefully controlled studies, and when they should be made available for compassionate reasons... According to Feng Li, chief executive of Mabworks, his company was motivated to fight a global emergency, and so he entered into a licensing agreement with ZMapp's intellectual property rights holder... Robin Robinson, director of the Biomedical Advanced Research and Development Authority, part of the United States Department of Health and Human Services, said "They have not done all the testing that we would normally do for safety before these products would go into humans."... Zmapp is undergoing clinical trial testing in the USA and Sierra Leone.]

[It seems to me that MIL77 could be treated the same way as some new cancer drugs, which are released in the West for compassionate use and withdrawn if severe side effects are seen, achieving safety testing at the same time as therapy. - Mod.JW]

9 Jun 2015 Ghana: GlaxoSmithKline (GSK), Johnson & Johnson behind Ebola vaccines trial
http://www.starrfmonline.com/1.4334323
[This has a useful table "Which vaccines are being tested and where"]

11 Jun 2015: Ghana approves trial of Ebola vaccine
http://allafrica.com/stories/201506111164.html?viewall=1
[Despite protests from civil society, the Ghanaian Food and Drugs Authority (FDA) has given the nod for the commencement of Ebola vaccine trial in the country. The regulatory body in an official release signed by its chief executive, Hudu Mogtari, communicated its decision to approve the trial of the Ebola vaccine in Ghana]
[This is good news after the Coalition for Ghana's Independence Now (CGIN), and the Volta regional branch of the National Democratic Party (NDC) originally opposed the trial. - Mod.LK]

13 Jun 2015 Japan: Favipiravir [T-705, Avigan], a prophylactic treatment for Ebola contacts?
http://www.thelancet.com/journals/lancet/article/PIIS0140-6736%2815%2961095-9/fulltext?rss=yes

12 Jun 2015 USA: Employer best practices for epidemic preparedness
http://www.jdsupra.com/legalnews/ebola-fears-employer-best-practices-for-28985/
[This article discusses the role that U.S. governmental guidance plays in monitoring the spread of the Ebola virus, resources that are available to employers to prepare for difficult employment decisions, and legal hazards associated with prohibiting employees from coming to work because of the fear that they may have been exposed to the Ebola virus. It concludes by recommending 6 employer best practices for handling Ebola-in-the-workplace concerns. Ref: "Ebola Fears: Employer Best Practices for Epidemic Preparedness," by Brooke T. Iley and Anna D. Stockman was published in the 8 Jun 2015, edition of Bloomberg BNA Daily Labor Report. Reproduced with permission from Daily Labor Report, 109 DLR I-1, 6/8/15. Copyright 2015 by The Bureau of National Affairs, Inc. (800-372-1033) http://www.bna.com - Mod.LK]

12 Jun 2015: Drawing order from disorder to unravel Ebola's lethality
http://www.rsc.org/chemistryworld/2015/06/ebola-lethality-intrinsically-disordered-protein
[The virulence of Ebola virus strains appears to be innately linked to the degree of disorder in proteins that form their nucleocapsids http://pubs.rsc.org/en/Results?SearchText=doi:c5mb00240k]

