http://allafrica.com/stories/201506111809.html?viewall=1
[The G7, after the economies of Guinea, Liberia and Sierra Leone were badly damaged by the Ebola outbreak, have pledged to assist the 3 countries in their recovery processes, but without a specific budget target.]

11 Jun 2015 (UK): 2 London Jewish students raise GBP 34 000 [USD 52 900] for Ebola victims
http://www.jewishnews.co.uk/two-london-jewish-students-raise-34k-for-ebola-victims/
[Fund-raising activities included persuading a French teacher to allow them to shave his head if they raised GBP 10 000 (USD 15 560).]

12 Jun 2015 USA (PA): Lehigh Valley company wins USD 10 million contract for Ebola testing
http://www.nbcphiladelphia.com/news/local/Lehigh-Valley-Company-Wins-10-million-ebola-contract-307139611.html#ixzz3csZWc8oJ
[OraSure Technologies, based in the USA (Bethlehem, PA), announced on Fri [12 Jun 2015] that it received a 3-year contract for up to USD 10.4 million (USD 1.8 million initially, and USD 8.6 million for clinical and regulatory activities), from the US Department of Health and Human Services to advance a rapid, point-of-care Ebola antigen test it has already developed. The device delivers results within 20 min. The procedure uses a drop of blood or saliva on a test strip.]

